column1: How many employees does your company or organization have?
column2: Is your employer primarily a tech company/organization?
column3: Is your primary role within your company related to tech/IT?
column4: Does your employer provide mental health benefits as part of healthcare coverage?
column5: Do you know the options for mental health care available under your employer-provided coverage?
column6: Has your employer ever formally discussed mental health (for example, as part of a wellness campaign or other official communication)?
column7: Does your employer offer resources to learn more about mental health concerns and options for seeking help?
column8: Is your anonymity protected if you choose to take advantage of mental health or substance abuse treatment resources provided by your employer?
column9: If a mental health issue prompted you to request a medical leave from work, asking for that leave would be:

column13: Would you feel comfortable discussing a mental health disorder with your direct supervisor(s)?
column14: Do you feel that your employer takes mental health as seriously as physical health?
column15: Have you heard of or observed negative consequences for co-workers who have been open about mental health issues in your workplace?

column29: Would you bring up a mental health issue with a potential employer in an interview?

column32: How willing would you be to share with friends and family that you have a mental illness?
